    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="480"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d480">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003 C 73/41</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yung Kwai</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous oral exchange of views
                    regarding the time and place for the meeting of the Commission to investigate
                    and report upon extraterritoriality and administration of justice in China as
                    provided in a Resolution adopted by the Washington Conference, I have the honor
                    to inform you that my Government will be pleased to have the Commission meet at
                    Peking on November 1st, 1923.</p>
                <pb facs="0737" n="621" xml:id="pg_621"/>
                <p>Moreover, I am instructed to request that you will be so kind as to send formal
                    notifications to the Governments of all the interested Powers with regard to the
                    matter.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Yung Kwai</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
